Google and Apple already want to be in your pocket and on your wrist, and for their next battle the rivals are gunning for your car's dashboard. 

2015 will be the year Android Auto and Apple's CarPlay systems roll out to more cars and reach the mainstream.

But concerns have already been raised about how dangerous the software is for drivers and how much the tech giants will be able to track owners.

